<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>NYT &gt; Technology</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/section/technology</link><description>Technology industry news, commentary, and analysis, with reporting on big tech, startups, and internet culture. The New York Times is a hub for conversation about news and ideas.</description><atom:link rel="self" href="https://rss.nytimes.com/services/xml/rss/nyt/Technology.xml" type="application/rss+xml" /><item><title>China’s Moonshot AI Unveils Kimi Model, Threatening America’s Lead</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/17/business/china-ai-moonshot-kimi.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/17/business/china-ai-moonshot-kimi.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/17/business/china-ai-moonshot-kimi.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>China’s Moonshot AI unveiled a freely available artificial intelligence model that seemed to narrow the gap with cutting-edge offerings from U.S. tech companies.</description><dc:creator>Meaghan Tobin and Cade Metz</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 17 Jul 2026 19:13:57 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">China</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Open-Source Software</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Startup</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Anthropic</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US Foreign Policy</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/17/multimedia/Biz-China-Moonshot-ckzl/Biz-China-Moonshot-ckzl-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Go Nakamura/Reuters</media:credit><media:description>The Moonshot AI booth at the World Artificial Intelligence Conference on Friday in Shanghai. The company’s Kimi K3 model performed as well at some tasks as the leading models from U.S. firms.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Judge Dismisses Suit Accusing Apple of Failing to Limit Child Sex Abuse Material</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/15/technology/apple-lawsuit-child-sexual-abuse-dismissed.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/15/technology/apple-lawsuit-child-sexual-abuse-dismissed.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/15/technology/apple-lawsuit-child-sexual-abuse-dismissed.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The lawsuit highlighted concerns that the privacy of Apple’s iCloud allows illegal material to be easily stored and shared on the service.</description><dc:creator>Kalley Huang</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 18:58:17 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Rape</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Child Abuse</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cloud computing</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Lawsuits</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Child pornography</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Apple</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">iCloud</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Product liability</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Noël Wise</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Decisions and Verdicts</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Privacy</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/15/multimedia/15biz-apple-csam-fkvc/15biz-apple-csam-fkvc-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Karsten Moran for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>An Apple Store in Manhattan. Regulators are starting to pay attention to concerns that iCloud’s privacy makes it easier to share child sexual abuse material.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Data Centers to Add Billions in Power Costs in 13 States</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/14/business/energy-environment/pjm-electricity-prices-data-centers.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/14/business/energy-environment/pjm-electricity-prices-data-centers.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/14/business/energy-environment/pjm-electricity-prices-data-centers.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>A power auction conducted by a giant grid operator is expected to add $6.3 billion in additional charges to consumers and businesses because of electricity needs of data centers.</description><dc:creator>Ivan Penn</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 00:25:48 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Data center</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Electric power</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Price</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US states</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">PJM Interconnection</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Regulation and Deregulation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Federal Energy Regulatory Commission</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Governors</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Josh Shapiro</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Pennsylvania</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">Mid-Atlantic States (US)</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Federalism</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/14/multimedia/14biz-pjm-rates-sub-vjgq/14biz-pjm-rates-sub-vjgq-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Leah Millis/Reuters</media:credit><media:description>Northern Virginia is home to several data centers, including the Digital Realty Data Center in Ashburn.</media:description></media:content></item></channel></rss>